Content:: Bimal Rathnayake is a Sri Lankan politician and a member of the Parliament of Sri Lanka. He is a national organiser and political bureau member of the people's liberation front (JVP). He is a member of the Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna party.[1]  This article about a politician from North Western Province, Sri Lanka is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
